Activity Diagram 1: Blood Donation Process
Purpose

This activity diagram represents the workflow involved when a donor donates blood and the inventory is updated.

Activities Flow

Start

Donor arrives at blood bank

Staff verifies donor identity

Check donor eligibility

Age

Health condition

Last donation date

Decision

If donor eligible → proceed

If donor not eligible → stop process

Record blood donation

Update blood inventory

Store donation details in database

Display confirmation message

End


Start
  ↓
Verify Donor Details
  ↓
Check Eligibility
  ↓
[Eligible?]
   ├─ No → Display Not Eligible → End
   └─ Yes
        ↓
Record Donation
  ↓
Update Inventory
  ↓
Save to Database
  ↓
Confirmation Message
  ↓
End

Activity Diagram 2: Blood Request Processing
Purpose

This activity diagram shows how a blood request from a hospital or patient is handled.

Activities Flow

Start

Hospital/Patient submits blood request

System receives request

Check blood availability

Decision

If blood available

If blood not available

If available:

Approve request

Update inventory

Notify requester

If not available:

Reject request

Notify requester

End

Start
  ↓
Submit Blood Request
  ↓
Check Availability
  ↓
[Blood Available?]
   ├─ No → Reject Request → Notify User → End
   └─ Yes
        ↓
Approve Request
  ↓
Update Inventory
  ↓
Notify User
  ↓
End
